{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "In the case study, NAGTLDA successfully predicted associations, such as NEAT1-colon cancer, SOX2-OT-prostate cancer, and WT1-AScolorectal cancer, which were previously unknown in the dataset.",
    "He et al. [79] investigated the function of NEAT1 in colon cancer, and found that the expression of NEAT1 was significantly elevated in colon cancer cells in their experiments, which proved that NEAT1 indirectly promotes the occurrence of colon cancer.",
    "Song et al. [80] demonstrated that SOX2-OT inhibits the proliferation and metastasis of prostate cancer cells by interacting with other non-coding RNAs.",
    "This discovery provides a new therapeutic approach for the treatment of prostate cancer.",
    "Zhang et al. [81] experimentally demonstrated experimentally that WT1-AS was closely associated with overall survival in colorectal cancer."
  ],
